Tic-Tac-Toe is a two-player game played on a 3x3 grid. The first player is **X**, and the second player is **O**. Players take turns placing their symbol in an empty square. The goal is to get **three of your symbols in a row** â€“ vertically, horizontally, or diagonally â€“ before your opponent.

